This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the task of predicting user actions in recommendation systems. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a novel method for session-based recommendation that involves encoding information using different approaches. Additionally, it may belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it involves modeling inter-session item-level interactions. It could also belong to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category as it involves natural language processing and text-based recommendation. Finally, it may belong to the Computers and Society (cs.CY) sub-category as it deals with the ethical implications of recommendation systems.
